```sql
-- 1:1 extract of transactions with store details
SELECT
    t.transaction_id,
    t.customer_id,
    t.store_id,
    t.amount,
    t.transaction_date,
    COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city,
    COALESCE(s.region, '(unknown)') AS region
FROM transactions t
LEFT JOIN stores s
    ON s.store_id = t.store_id
```

-- stg_customer_channels.sql
```sql
-- 1:1 extract of customer attributions, keeping earliest channel per customer
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        attributed_at,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM customer_channels
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel,
    attributed_at
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_customer_enriched.sql
```sql
-- Join customers with their attributed channel, handling nulls
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        c.customer_id,
        c.name,
        c.email,
        c.signup_date,
        COALESCE(cc.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel
    FROM customers c
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }} cc
        ON cc.customer_id = c.customer_id
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    name,
    email,
    signup_date,
    channel
FROM source
```

-- fct_customer_revenue_by_channel.sql
```sql
-- Customer revenue aggregated by attribution channel and city
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        ce.customer_id,
        ce.channel,
        t.city,
        t.amount
    FROM {{ ref('int_customer_enriched') }} ce
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
        ON t.customer_id = ce.customer_id
)
SELECT
    channel,
    city,
    SUM(amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(DISTINCT transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM source
WHERE amount IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY
    channel,
    city
ORDER BY
    channel ASC,
    city ASC
